job_description:
This is Worldline
We are the innovators at the heart of the payments technology industry, shaping how the world pays and gets paid. The solutions our people build today power the growth of millions of businesses tomorrow. From your local coffee shop to unicorns and international banks. From San Francisco to Auckland. We are in every corner of the world, in every part of commerce. And just as we help our customers accelerate their business, we are committed to helping our people accelerate their careers. Together, we shape the evolution.
The Opportunity
At Worldline, our technology addresses persistent challenges of the payment world. We design and operate leading digital payment and transactional solutions that enable sustainable economic growth and reinforce trust and security in our societies. If you are a recent (law) graduate, with 0-3 years of experience, interested in learning the inner workings of a compliance department within a regulated fast-paced multinational as well as gaining exposure to the exciting world of FinTech, then get ready to join our company.
We have many hardworking and dedicated peers that give the best they can every day. We are committed to continuous improvement. We are always looking for new and innovative ways to improve quality, reduce costs, build excellent solutions, and grow customer happiness. We would like to welcome an organized, innovative and process driven colleague to our Financial Security Compliance Team. Eager to learn and the willingness to develop yourself are key. In addition, a critical mindset and pragmatic approach are desired.
You will work for Worldline Digital Commerce (Global Collect Services B.V. and subsidiaries) based in Hoofddorp, close to Amsterdam. Global Collect Services B.V. has a PSD2 license and is supervised by DNB. Worldline Digital Commerce provides one single integration with our global payment platform and connects merchants to markets around the world. Over 150 payment methods and currencies deliver a fully localized payment experience to customers anywhere, on any device. With our Full-Service model merchants are able to collect those payments from around the world without the need for a local bank account or legal entity. The merchants of Worldline Digital Commerce are large global enterprises.
Day-to-Day Responsibilities
The Financial Crime Officer will be working together with the other compliance officers in the following areas:
Develop and execute the Financial Security Annual Plan;
Develop and execute the Financial Security Monitoring Programme;
Conduct Compliance Monitoring on financial crime related topics;
Manage and carry out the Systematic Integrity Risk Analyses;
Provide in-depth training and awareness sessions on financial crime related topics;
Advice other organisational departments on financial crime related topics;
Further professionalize the transaction monitoring framework;
Further professionalize the sanction screening process;
Develop and review policies and procedures on financial crime related topics;
Conduct gap analyses on (new) laws and regulations related to financial crime;
Assist in completing DNB questionnaires and reports;
Develop Compliance Reports for the Financial Security compliance pillar;
Manage compliance oversight by creating dashboards of compliance risks (using e.g. software).
What We Are Looking For
You are following a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree;
You’re interested in compliance and EU Regulations in financial services (e.g., PSD2);
Business oriented, bearing in mind the bigger picture with the compliance risks and independent of mind.
Capacity to search for answers and solve problems, capacity to focus on the final objective.
Interpersonal skills and relationship management.
Capacity to work independently.
Strong team player with high self-motivation and positive attitude.
Eager to learn and the willingness to develop yourself are key.
A critical mindset and pragmatic approach are desired.
Able to read Dutch (Dutch laws).
Perfect fluency (oral and written) in English.
Knowledge in payment industry and payment services is nice to have.
Perks & Benefits
At Worldline you’ll get the chance to be at the heart of the global payments technology industry and shape how the world pays and gets paid. On top of that, you will also:
Use your 29.5 holiday days, based on 40 work hours, to enjoy some time off and recharge!
On target bonus based on your personal performance and the company results.
We pay for your commute when working from the Worldline office.
We offer flexible working hours, so you can adapt to your personal circumstances. Working from home is possible too!
We care for your health. Enjoy the discount on your Health insurance!
You become a member of our pension scheme. Next to the savings we make, you have the option to make savings for when you retire!
Joining the big-league means entering a world of knowledge and wisdom for you to opt-in to. Connect with likeminded colleagues, learn from the best and grow!
Shape the evolution
We are on an exciting journey towards the next frontiers of payments technology, and we look for big thinkers, people with passion, can-do attitude and a hunger to learn and grow. Here you’ll work with ambitious colleagues from around the world, take on unique challenges as a team, and make a real impact on the society. With an empowering culture, strong technology and extensive training opportunities, we help you accelerate your career - wherever you decide to go. Join our global team of 18,000 innovators and shape a tomorrow that is yours to own.

Senior Corporate Officer
Location: Amsterdam, Netherlands
Date Posted: Mar 15, 2023
Description
Senior Corporate Officer
AMSTERDAM
Department: Client Team
Employment Type: Full Time
Permanent location: Amsterdam
About Apex:
The Apex Group is a global financial services provider with 10,000+ staff across 70+ offices globally. We look to recruit bright, articulate and numerate employees who are not afraid of a challenge and are prepared to work hard and love what they do.
Every employee plays a part in making Apex who we are today and the more that we grow, the more important that becomes. Whatever your career path or specialism Apex provides a global platform to allow you to thrive.

The Position:
As a Senior Corporate Officer you will work closely with Client Director(s), Manager and (Senior) Financial Officer(s). Within the client portfolio of the Teams Client Director(s), the Senior Corporate Officer is responsible for all legal matters. The Senior Corporate Officer will provide legal services, depending on the client's wishes and feasibility in quality and timeliness of the agreed services. You are able to handle complex issues and to solve ad hoc problems.
Competently and autonomously manage a more complex workload. Carry out duties in a professional manner and in accordance with policies and procedures, legal/regulatory requirements, service levels and company standards so as to meet with business expectations. Where applicable assist in managing the team and deputising in the Manager’s absence.

Role and Key Responsibilities:
Assessing whether documents can be signed, having due regard for both the position of Apex Financial Services B.V. (Apex) in its capacity as manager, and the interests of the client entities;
Timely detection of tax and / or legal aspects of a proposed transaction and to involve specialists, in consultation with all those concerned;
Guiding clients in relation to Dutch company law;
Identifies, investigates and helps to resolve issues / questions on legal, fiscal and administrative level and involves specialists when necessary;
Maintaining contacts with advisers and clients and proactively building upon those relationships;
The ability to accordingly represent Apex with external relations;
Maintaining contact and conduct correspondence with authorities;
Ensuring compliance with the relevant laws and regulations on supervision;
Ensuring customer acceptance and periodic reviews, keeping in mind the various risks relating to services provided by Apex;
Establishing client companies, in close cooperation with notary, bank etc.;
Accept Directorship role of client companies, subject to approval of Apex;

Contributing to and monitoring of high quality standards;
Compliance with and monitoring of internal procedures;
Supervising the Corporate and Support Officers.

Your profile:
A completed study Dutch, notarial and / or tax law;
Approximately three to five years+ relevant work experience at a trust office, law firm, tax advisory or notary office or as a corporate lawyer in the area of corporate and business law;
Willingness to increase legal and tax knowledge;
Features numerical and analytical skills;
Ability to oversee issues at client companies from a more comprehensive viewpoint ("helicopter view") and the ability to make connections with other disciplines;
Communication skills, both externally and internally;
Experienced in the use of the Dutch and English language in the preparation of documents and in oral and written communication to clients. The mastery of another language is an advantage;
Strong customer focus and be able to build a long term relationship with clients;
Reliable, proactive, decisive;
Flexible and be able to cope well with deadlines;
Team player with responsibility and commitment;
You are re looking for the challenge / development in the field of business development and (account) management, using your legal / tax knowledge.
What you will get in return:
A high level of visibility within a large organisation on an upwards trajectory
The ability to define marketing processes to drive innovation and have a tangible impact on the business
Be part of a dynamic and fast-paced team that makes a genuine impact on client service delivery.
Exposure to all aspects of the business, cross-jurisdiction and to working with senior management directly.
Opportunity to work with a diverse, agile and global team.
The opportunity to innovate, bring discipline to brand activity and really make a difference.
Additional information:
We are an equal opportunity employer and ensure that no applicant is subject to less favourable treatment on the grounds of gender, gender identity, marital status, race, colour, nationality, ethnicity, age, sexual orientation, socio-economic, responsibilities for dependants, physical or mental disability. Any hiring decision are made on the basis of skills, qualifications and experiences.
For more information on our commitment to Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) please visit https://theapexgroup.com/csr-policy/
